1
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,400
Cao Deyong

2
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,080
Present.

3
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:40,600
Joined the mill in 2004 to learn sheet forming.

4
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,040
Chief Papermaker for 16 years.

5
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:42,920
Zhang Qingliang

6
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,360
Present.

7
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:45,400
Joined the mill in 2001 to learn sheet forming.

8
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:46,800
Chief Papermaker for 18 years.

9
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:47,720
Man Xiaochuan

10
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:48,400
Present.

11
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:50,200
Eight years in sheet forming.

12
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:51,400
Ye Shengkai

13
00:01:51,400 --> 00:01:52,040
Present.

14
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,320
Provincial-level heritage inheritor of sheet forming.

15
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:56,880
Huang...

16
00:01:56,880 --> 00:01:58,480
That's fine, no need for introductions.

17
00:01:58,480 --> 00:01:59,160
Master.

18
00:02:01,200 --> 00:02:01,880
Xiao Man.

19
00:02:01,960 --> 00:02:02,520
Master.

20
00:02:03,320 --> 00:02:04,200
Are you doing all right?

21
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:05,920
Not as good as at the Xuan family's.

22
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,560
But I like hearing that.

23
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,880
Your Madam would love to hear that even more.

24
00:02:13,720 --> 00:02:14,280
Magan'er.

25
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:14,840
Master.

26
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:17,840
Look at that, Magan'er's filled out nicely.

27
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,320
So Master's saying I've gotten fat.

28
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,280
Found yourself a girlfriend yet?

29
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:26,240
Just started seeing one, she does paper trimming.

30
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,720
That's wonderful.

31
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,080
Your Madam does paper trimming too.

32
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:30,880
Just like me.

33
00:02:33,480 --> 00:02:34,280
Lao Ye.

34
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:37,080
Lao Xuan.

35
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:39,320
Master Xuan.

36
00:02:40,360 --> 00:02:41,920
I know you two go way back.

37
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:43,640
So I made a point of telling Shi Quan.

38
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,160
Master Ye.

39
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,200
Lao Ye.

40
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:48,400
I appreciate the thought.

41
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,000
I've been thinking.

42
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,640
As for you...

43
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:54,080
You've earned all the honors you deserve.

44
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,080
This time,

45
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,280
could you step aside for the young ones?

46
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,080
Make way for the next generation.

47
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:06,600
All right, I'll follow your lead.

48
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,360
Good brother.

49
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,440
No need for introductions.

50
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:13,840
Every one of you is top-notch.

51
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:15,840
All the masters here,

52
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,280
we already know.

53
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,600
And we know them well.

54
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,440
Wei Jianzhi.

55
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,120
He's the captain of your Chief Papermaker team.

56
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,560
Anyone who doubts him

57
00:03:26,560 --> 00:03:28,080
can challenge him at sheet forming.

58
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,360
If you can't beat him,

59
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:30,800
then fall in line.

60
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:33,200
Forty-four people,

61
00:03:33,560 --> 00:03:35,400
eighty-eight hands,

62
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:38,080
must move like a single pair of hands.

63
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:39,960
To pull this off,

64
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:41,320
we must unite as one,

65
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:42,760
think as one,

66
00:03:42,760 --> 00:03:44,200
and pull together.

67
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:45,680
Wei Jianzhi,

68
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:48,400
get everyone acquainted in a bit.

69
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:50,520
Does anyone have any questions?

70
00:03:50,760 --> 00:03:51,640
None.

71
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:54,240
Good.

72
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:57,800
Old Man,

73
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,080
this pulley-and-machinery setup,

74
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:03,320
it's fantastic.

75
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,760
The moment I saw it,

76
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:07,920
all the worries I'd been carrying,

77
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,880
all those difficulties I'd imagined,

78
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:11,880
are completely solved.

79
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,520
Lao Xuan,

80
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:17,720
it's not easy earning a compliment from you.

81
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,760
I say we finalize the personnel.

82
00:04:19,959 --> 00:04:21,000
No time to waste.

83
00:04:21,079 --> 00:04:23,560
Let's aim to start trial sheet forming the day after tomorrow.

84
00:04:23,560 --> 00:04:24,200
What do you think?

85
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,000
Good, good, good.

86
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,320
Then the paper trimmers and paper dryers,

87
00:04:27,320 --> 00:04:28,520
we've got to lock them in too, right?

88
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:32,640
For paper drying, I want Wu Tongfang.

89
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:34,240
I know this man well.

90
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:36,480
There's no need to consider anyone else.

91
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:41,880
Not enough.

92
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,520
Raise it two more degrees.

93
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:44,320
Master.

94
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,640
This is already the usual drying temperature here.

95
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,000
Do as I say.

96
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:51,400
Raise it two more degrees.

97
00:04:51,520 --> 00:04:51,920
Hurry.

98
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,600
Yes, Master.

99
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:53,920
Master.

100
00:04:54,080 --> 00:04:55,160
Eleven point four meters long,

101
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,200
positioning the sheet is no easy task.

102
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:57,800
Even the slightest tilt,

103
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,320
and it'll slip off the drying wall at the far end.

104
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,240
Then the paper's ruined.

105
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:03,200
That's exactly why Xuan Yongnian came to me.

106
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:04,600
Come on, come on.

107
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:06,280
Over here, gather round.

108
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:09,520
Master Xuan.

109
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,640
The finest paper trimmers in this factory

110
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,320
are all right here.

111
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,120
Pick one to be the captain.

112
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:17,840
Masters, please hold out your right hands.

113
00:05:17,880 --> 00:05:18,760
Let me take a look.

114
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,120
You've done paper trimming

115
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,520
for a good twenty years now, right?

116
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:36,240
Twenty-two years.

117
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,200
Good.

118
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,520
Here, do this.

119
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,040
Your foot,

120
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:42,640
lift it up, let me see the sole.

121
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:49,360
Good. This foot.

122
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:54,800
She'll be our paper trimming captain.

123
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:55,800
Wonderful.

124
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,760
Thank you, everyone.

125
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:58,760
This...

126
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,880
This Lao Xuan,

127
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,880
he's got a truly sharp eye.

128
00:06:07,080 --> 00:06:08,680
Wait, what does that mean?

129
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:10,640
Paper trimming.

130
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:12,800
These two sides here,

131
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,920
you're always rubbing against the paper edge.

132
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:17,000
The thicker the calluses you build up,

133
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,920
the more experience it shows.

134
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,200
As for the soles,

135
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,320
both sides wear down evenly.

136
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:26,040
That means when pushing the blade to trim,

137
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:27,240
her balance doesn't shift.

138
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:29,440
Stands steady, moves steady.

139
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:36,880
This Master Xuan...

140
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:39,040
Chairman, please don't worry.

141
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,080
We've finished picking everyone.

142
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,240
Right now,

143
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:44,320
we're selecting material in the processed bark workshop.

144
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,880
Master Xuan is very satisfied.

145
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,240
We expect that the day after tomorrow

146
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,440
we can begin the trial sheet forming.

147
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,280
Good.

148
00:06:50,760 --> 00:06:51,560
Rest assured.

149
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:52,960
I've got this handled.

150
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,160
Good.

151
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,520
Goodbye, Chairman.

152
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:56,080
Lao Xuan.

153
00:06:57,200 --> 00:06:57,880
Director Man.

154
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,200
So, what's wrong?

155
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,920
The processed straw is fine,

156
00:07:03,440 --> 00:07:04,760
but he's not happy with the processed bark.

157
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,680
He's seen samples from all three bases.

158
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:09,560
All of them. This is already the best material.

159
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,560
So what do we do?

160
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,680
Lao Xuan really has changed.

161
00:07:16,880 --> 00:07:18,360
With his old temper,

162
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:20,480
he'd have torn the roof off this workshop.

163
00:07:20,560 --> 00:07:21,760
Now he doesn't say a word,

164
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,880
just sits there sulking.

165
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:26,360
We didn't think it through well enough.

166
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,760
Old Man.

167
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,240
I've got an idea.

168
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,680
Let's go find Xie Tianyu.

169
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:31,880
Old Xie...

170
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:36,000
We haven't been in touch with him for ages.

171
00:07:37,320 --> 00:07:38,720
What about your drying yard?

172
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,560
Old Lin went off to Shanghai this year.

173
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:45,240
Zhang Du's the only one watching my drying yard now.

174
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:48,680
Old Xie's skill in making processed bark,

175
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,160
that's a heaven-sent gift.

176
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,000
When it comes to processed bark and straw,

177
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,160
Old Xie is the only man I truly respect.

178
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:56,720
Then let's go to his place right now.

179
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:59,440
Right, we'll go now.

180
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:00,080
Let's go.

181
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:16,680
Lao Xuan

182
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,320
This really won't do.

183
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,240
Lao Xuan

184
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:46,960
This won't do

185
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:50,720
Xie Mingxiang

186
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:54,320
Did your dad make these?

187
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,440
One look

188
00:08:56,880 --> 00:08:58,280
and I can tell you never bought our bark

189
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,480
He passed away two years ago

190
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:02,360
He's gone

191
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,520
Worked himself to death making processed bark

192
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:06,880
You want it or not?

193
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:08,440
If you do, I'll give you a discount

194
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:13,880
Your dad's craftsmanship

195
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:17,760
was respected by every Xuan paper maker

196
00:09:18,560 --> 00:09:19,280
Let me ask you

197
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,440
how did you end up learning it this poorly?

198
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,160
If it makes money, it's a craft

199
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:27,000
If it doesn't make money

200
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,520
then it's all worthless crap

201
00:09:30,200 --> 00:09:31,440
My wife works away from home

202
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,560
and I stay home to raise our second kid

203
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:34,240
I only do this lousy job because I have no choice

204
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,240
Working myself ragged and still can't earn a dime

205
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,240
Worse off than a junk collector

206
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,000
Craft, my foot

207
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:43,680
How about this

208
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,840
Could you take me

209
00:09:48,160 --> 00:09:50,080
to visit your dad's grave?

210
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,840
Xiao Xie

211
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,600
I was wrong to blame you

212
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:14,240
I really admire people who honor their parents

213
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:32,880
Let me say a few words.

214
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:33,760
Go ahead.

215
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:37,000
Old Xie.

216
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:43,960
I remember you once told me,

217
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,800
making processed bark and straw

218
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:49,960
is trading human hide for tree bark.

219
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,760
This work of processing bark and straw,

220
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:55,360
you've done it your whole life.

221
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,520
To make the finest Xuan paper,

222
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:02,200
on your own body,

223
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,720
who knows how many layers of skin you shed.

224
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,600
But the work you produced,

225
00:11:08,760 --> 00:11:10,520
it was truly beautiful.

226
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,520
I, Xuan Yongnian, deeply admire you.

227
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:19,840
Everyone who makes Xuan paper admires you.

228
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,160
It's a great pity,

229
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:24,840
once you're gone,

230
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:28,280
there'll be no successor.

231
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,280
Lao Xuan.

232
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,080
How about this,

233
00:11:37,640 --> 00:11:38,880
we go back to the factory,

234
00:11:39,120 --> 00:11:41,520
and pick the best we can from the material storage.

235
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,760
The best of a bad lot, I guess.

236
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:48,680
Old Man.

237
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,840
Anyone else can say that,

238
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,440
but you can't say it!

239
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:56,120
You're right.

240
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,360
I shouldn't have said that.

241
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,760
But, but we've run out of options, haven't we?

242
00:12:03,520 --> 00:12:04,360
How about

243
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:06,120
we go take a look at your drying yard.

244
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:07,880
Let's go.

245
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,720
This material is truly excellent

246
00:12:45,640 --> 00:12:47,040
Look how well this is done

247
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,480
Without eight or nine months of work

248
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,840
you'd never dry it this well

249
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,280
That's right

250
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,280
This is just wonderful

251
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:55,240
I've searched high and low

252
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:57,000
and here it is, right in my hands

253
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:01,680
Old Man

254
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,440
That's Zhang Du, isn't it?

255
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:06,480
This boy's like a completely different person

256
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,760
Look at how he handles the processed bark

257
00:13:09,280 --> 00:13:10,800
He looks just like a seasoned master

258
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,960
I really never expected

259
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:22,640
he'd do it this well

260
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:26,040
Truly white as snow, strong as sinew

261
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:28,640
He's got no two strips overlapping

262
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:29,840
and not a single stone is visible

263
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:31,520
He's taken the craft to its very peak

264
00:13:31,520 --> 00:13:32,920
How could it not be good?

265
00:13:36,640 --> 00:13:37,440
Lao Xuan

266
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:39,800
You've got a worthy successor

267
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:44,760
A worthy successor indeed

268
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:53,880
Zhang Du

269
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:59,240
Well done, lad!

270
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,360
That Zhang Du, honestly

271
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:18,160
Your dad asked him back, so he should just come

272
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:21,640
But no, he can't bear to leave the dried processed bark

273
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,880
There's hardly anyone making paper now

274
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:26,520
Who's going to steal it?

275
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,600
We're not even making paper anymore

276
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,200
Whether he'll even come back is another matter

277
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:34,520
That's exactly what hurts your dad the most

278
00:14:34,960 --> 00:14:36,880
He dried so much fine processed bark

279
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:39,320
Not making paper, not selling it either

280
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:40,840
Such a shame

281
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:42,760
Where's Dad?

282
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
He was just here packing things with me

283
00:14:46,920 --> 00:14:48,880
The Three-Zhang-Three goes into its first trial tomorrow

284
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:52,120
He insists on staying at the factory himself

285
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:53,120
To keep an eye on things personally

286
00:14:53,360 --> 00:14:54,480
He just doesn't think it through

287
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,320
