557
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:23,960
We can understand that.

558
00:28:24,600 --> 00:28:27,360
But we don't have 44 sheet-forming

559
00:28:27,800 --> 00:28:29,000
strongmen.

560
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:34,920
Old Man.

561
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,000
I feel like everyone here

562
00:28:39,360 --> 00:28:41,400
still lacks that fighting spirit.

563
00:28:42,360 --> 00:28:44,440
The factory's production quota is huge.

564
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:46,800
The pressure on us is enormous too.

565
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,600
One, two, three!

566
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:51,560
One, two, three!

567
00:28:52,040 --> 00:28:52,960
One, two, three!

568
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:53,720
Old Man.

569
00:28:54,840 --> 00:28:56,160
Give me a little more time.

570
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:57,480
Tomorrow,

571
00:28:58,560 --> 00:28:59,520
I'll do it myself.

572
00:29:00,520 --> 00:29:02,720
Are you... are you up to it?

573
00:29:04,480 --> 00:29:05,320
I have to be, even if I'm not.

574
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:06,600
One, two, three!

575
00:29:07,120 --> 00:29:08,600
One, two, three!

576
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:10,080
One, two, three!

577
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:13,120
We've worked ourselves to the bone.

578
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:14,600
We've formed over a hundred sheets,

579
00:29:15,040 --> 00:29:16,960
and not one of them passed.

580
00:29:17,800 --> 00:29:19,000
And that's not even the worst part.

581
00:29:19,360 --> 00:29:20,280
The real problem is,

582
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:22,760
the sheets we're forming

583
00:29:22,760 --> 00:29:24,040
are far short of the standard.

584
00:29:24,040 --> 00:29:25,160
Now that's a real problem.

585
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:27,400
Expecting results in a short time

586
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:28,280
is simply impossible.

587
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:30,760
Within a week, it'll all fall apart.

588
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,160
Don't believe me? Just watch.

589
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:33,520
A week, you say?

590
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:34,760
Haven't you heard?

591
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:37,240
Tomorrow, Sunday, is the last day.

592
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,160
If we can't form a sheet tomorrow,

593
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:40,920
they'll all fall apart.

594
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,240
Xuan Yan.

595
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:47,240
Could you have gotten here any later?

596
00:29:48,520 --> 00:29:50,600
Our President Xin spends more time with you

597
00:29:50,600 --> 00:29:52,000
each day than he does with me.

598
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,440
I'm getting jealous.

599
00:29:54,080 --> 00:29:54,480
President Xin.

600
00:29:54,480 --> 00:29:54,920
Don't talk nonsense.

601
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:55,720
Come, come, have a seat.

602
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:58,400
We've got a design to finalize today.

603
00:29:58,400 --> 00:29:59,320
I'm swamped.

604
00:29:59,320 --> 00:30:00,000
No need, please, have a seat.

605
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:00,800
Sit, sit, sit down.

606
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:01,520
Thank you.

607
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:03,760
How's it going, everyone? Enjoying the drinks?

608
00:30:03,760 --> 00:30:05,040
Good sheet forming today, huh?

609
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,080
Are you kidding?

610
00:30:06,200 --> 00:30:07,480
We formed over a hundred sheets,

611
00:30:07,720 --> 00:30:08,760
and not one of them passed.

612
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:12,600
What's going on?

613
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:15,960
We can form the sheets, sure,

614
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:17,720
but they tear up badly.

615
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:20,080
Right now, every sheet we form is a reject.

616
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:22,240
The key problem is this.

617
00:30:22,560 --> 00:30:24,000
Coordinating this many people,

618
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:25,760
we've never done it before.

619
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,720
Master wants us to practice more,

620
00:30:27,720 --> 00:30:29,520
but I don't think practice is the issue.

621
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:31,600
Xuan Yan.

622
00:30:31,920 --> 00:30:32,960
Let me say something.

623
00:30:33,360 --> 00:30:34,200
When you go back,

624
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,840
try hard to talk sense into your old man.

625
00:30:36,240 --> 00:30:38,600
Let President Xiao handle the Chief Papermaker role.

626
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,040
That Wei Jianzhi

627
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:41,720
can't hold down a stage this big.

628
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:43,960
It's not like we haven't told my dad.

629
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,280
But you know my old man's temper.

630
00:30:45,280 --> 00:30:46,360
It's not like you don't know it.

631
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:47,560
Push him too much and he gets fed up.

632
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:48,960
And besides,

633
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:50,520
tomorrow is the last day.

634
00:30:50,800 --> 00:30:52,240
If we can't form a sheet tomorrow,

635
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:54,800
the workers will all quit.

636
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:56,320
No way, is it really that serious?

637
00:31:32,760 --> 00:31:34,520
If you can really paint on it

638
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:37,760
I, Xuan Yongnian, will surely make it

639
00:31:37,920 --> 00:31:39,680
The Three-Zhang-Three you want

640
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:41,920
If you can make it

641
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:43,520
Then I'll surely paint

642
00:31:44,360 --> 00:31:45,720
If you can paint

643
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,920
Then I'll surely make it

644
00:31:49,760 --> 00:31:52,400
Just for this paper of yours

645
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,400
I won't die

646
00:31:56,320 --> 00:31:58,720
A gentleman's word

647
00:32:01,240 --> 00:32:03,000
is his bond

648
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,320
Hello?

649
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:31,800
Is this Mr. Jiang?

650
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:35,160
This is Xuan Yongnian from Jing County, Xuancheng.

651
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:37,240
Hello, Uncle Xuan.

652
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:39,200
Hello, hello.

653
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:41,760
I just wanted to ask,

654
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:46,040
how has Master Jiang been doing lately?

655
00:32:46,920 --> 00:32:48,520
For the time being,

656
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:50,160
the radiation and chemo have gone all right.

657
00:32:50,440 --> 00:32:51,760
He's pretty much stable.

658
00:32:52,720 --> 00:32:53,800
Can he recover?

659
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:55,560
I'm afraid not.

660
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,600
The cancer cells have already spread.

661
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:01,560
They've spread.

662
00:33:06,720 --> 00:33:07,680
Actually, I...

663
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:12,000
I shouldn't be asking about this,

664
00:33:12,360 --> 00:33:13,960
because right now I'm hard at work

665
00:33:13,960 --> 00:33:15,600
making the Three-Zhang-Three Xuan paper.

666
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:17,280
I want to know,

667
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:19,120
did the doctor say

668
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,480
how much time is left?

669
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,960
Maybe just two or three months.

670
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:27,440
The doctor can't really predict it.

671
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:29,560
He said my dad's holding on

672
00:33:30,520 --> 00:33:32,240
purely by clinging to life.

673
00:33:32,600 --> 00:33:33,920
My dad also said

674
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:36,200
that once the Three-Zhang-Three is done,

675
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:38,000
he wants to inspect it himself.

676
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:40,000
I understand, I understand.

677
00:33:40,800 --> 00:33:42,600
I won't keep you, I won't keep you.

678
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:09,760
Master

679
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:15,679
I came to see you

680
00:34:15,840 --> 00:34:16,679
Please, have a seat

681
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:29,040
These dishes are freshly cooked, still hot

682
00:34:31,080 --> 00:34:33,199
I already ate at the canteen

683
00:34:33,719 --> 00:34:35,080
And I'm not hungry anyway

684
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:40,760
Then let me have a few drinks with you

685
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:45,239
It's been a long time since we drank together

686
00:34:52,360 --> 00:34:53,159
Master

687
00:35:04,520 --> 00:35:05,280
These past few days

688
00:35:06,120 --> 00:35:07,160
you've worked so hard

689
00:35:31,200 --> 00:35:32,040
These past few days

690
00:35:32,960 --> 00:35:34,240
I've been thinking too

691
00:35:35,520 --> 00:35:37,080
about why this sheet won't form

692
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:39,320
We all know

693
00:35:39,320 --> 00:35:41,280
a mould frame gets heavier once it soaks up water

694
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:42,600
And on top of that,

695
00:35:43,520 --> 00:35:44,880
a mould frame this big

696
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:47,040
So I think

697
00:35:47,520 --> 00:35:49,520
even with the finest fir wood,

698
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:52,320
after going in and out of the water,

699
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:56,640
this mould frame will warp at least a little

700
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:59,920
If the two sides don't control their force well,

701
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:04,680
the pulp will form an S-shape on the mould frame

702
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:08,280
and then the sheet won't come out even

703
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,600
On the surface,

704
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:11,800
with more people,

705
00:36:12,680 --> 00:36:15,360
the balance of force and the pressure

706
00:36:15,720 --> 00:36:17,760
become very hard to keep consistent

707
00:36:18,520 --> 00:36:19,280
But

708
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:21,720
at a deeper level,

709
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:24,840
I'm getting old

710
00:36:26,480 --> 00:36:28,560
Jiang Ziliu is clinging to life right now

711
00:36:28,560 --> 00:36:30,840
And me? I fall just short

712
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,120
I can't hold on anymore

713
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:38,720
Master

714
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:45,000
Your apprentice will hold on right there with you

715
00:36:58,960 --> 00:37:00,520
The old masters now,

716
00:37:02,520 --> 00:37:04,360
they've lost the drive for it.

717
00:37:06,280 --> 00:37:07,720
If tomorrow,

718
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,280
we fail again,

719
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:15,480
then the Three-Zhang-Three gets scrapped.

720
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,000
So tomorrow, no matter what,

721
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,800
even if it kills me,

722
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:26,000
I've got to step in myself.

723
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:37,120
Lao Xuan.

724
00:37:38,200 --> 00:37:41,000
The bubbles and water holes are easy to fix.

725
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,840
The biggest problem now

726
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:44,720
is this unevenness.

727
00:37:50,160 --> 00:37:50,760
Master.

728
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:53,520
This just won't work.

729
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,720
An old lady's foot-binding cloth

730
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:58,520
is probably smoother than this paper.

731
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:01,040
There's no way to dry it.

732
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:03,040
Let's just go back and do it properly,

733
00:38:03,240 --> 00:38:04,560
drying the small sheets.

734
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:06,520
What if...

735
00:38:06,560 --> 00:38:07,920
There's no "what if."

736
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,200
Master Xuan.

737
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,800
Master Xuan, we won't wait here anymore.

738
00:38:12,800 --> 00:38:14,520
It's been ten days already.

739
00:38:14,560 --> 00:38:17,400
We'll head back to dry our small sheets.

740
00:38:18,120 --> 00:38:19,360
You all keep at it.

741
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:21,160
Let's go.

742
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:24,840
All right then.

743
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:27,760
Let's do something.

744
00:38:27,760 --> 00:38:29,360
Forget the sheet forming for now.

745
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:31,800
Now follow my orders.

746
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,960
I'll stand over there.

747
00:38:34,080 --> 00:38:35,200
Face me.

748
00:38:35,720 --> 00:38:36,880
Line up, quick!

749
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:37,960
Come on, hurry up.

750
00:38:37,960 --> 00:38:39,360
Faster, faster!

751
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:41,680
Face me.

752
00:38:50,080 --> 00:38:53,320
Numbers two, four, six, eight, ten,

753
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:54,360
and so on,

754
00:38:55,160 --> 00:38:57,240
step to the sides, form four rows.

755
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:59,440
Lengthwise, facing me.

756
00:39:00,440 --> 00:39:01,640
Now, what we'll do

757
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:04,160
is a little game, a little contest.

758
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:05,760
What... what contest, Master?

759
00:39:05,760 --> 00:39:06,400
What contest?

760
00:39:07,760 --> 00:39:08,800
Arm wrestling.

761
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:09,760
Arm wrestling?

762
00:39:10,880 --> 00:39:11,640
Now these two rows,

763
00:39:11,640 --> 00:39:12,640
this is getting interesting.

764
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:14,280
Face each other, quick!

765
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:15,320
What's so interesting?

766
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:16,520
Lock hands.

767
00:39:17,040 --> 00:39:19,360
Looks like your master's given up on sheet forming.

768
00:39:19,360 --> 00:39:19,800
Crouch down.

769
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:21,320
Playing games instead.

770
00:39:21,520 --> 00:39:22,320
Keep an eye out.

771
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:24,000
Wait for my signal.

772
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:26,400
Everyone on the sides, cheer them on.

773
00:39:26,520 --> 00:39:28,360
One, two, three!

774
00:39:28,720 --> 00:39:29,960
Come on, come on!

775
00:39:29,960 --> 00:39:31,160
Come on, come on!

776
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:32,320
Come on!

777
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:36,160
You lot, step back.

778
00:39:36,160 --> 00:39:37,880
Masters in the back, come forward.

779
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:40,800
Crouch down.

780
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,280
Lock hands.

781
00:39:46,160 --> 00:39:47,920
You think there's a chance

782
00:39:49,040 --> 00:39:50,720
he's finding the strongest arm

783
00:39:51,560 --> 00:39:52,760
to consider replacing the Chief Papermaker?

784
00:39:52,760 --> 00:39:53,440
Start!

785
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:55,840
Come on, come on!

786
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:57,680
What does this have to do with the Chief Papermaker?

787
00:39:58,040 --> 00:39:58,920
If you ask me,

788
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,520
just replace the team leader.

789
00:40:01,160 --> 00:40:02,400
Changing the general is like changing the blade.

790
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,880
Put Bro Min in charge and it's all sorted.

791
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:05,760
All right, all right, keep it down, keep it down.

792
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:07,640
Good.

793
00:40:08,920 --> 00:40:10,360
Masters who won,

794
00:40:10,640 --> 00:40:12,240
go to that side of the paper vat.

795
00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:13,520
Masters who lost,

796
00:40:13,520 --> 00:40:15,040
stay on this side of the vat.

797
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:15,680
Quick.

798
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:16,440
Go.

799
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:19,640
Quick, quick, quick!

800
00:40:19,640 --> 00:40:20,360
Go.

801
00:40:25,800 --> 00:40:27,120
Lean into the water.

802
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:29,440
Go take a look.

803
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:30,400
Stand steady.

804
00:40:34,560 --> 00:40:36,320
Why am I doing this?

805
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:37,800
It's because

806
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,640
the winners take the Chief Papermaker role,

807
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:42,600
the losers become the Sheet-lifters.

808
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:46,520
This way everyone's strength stays balanced.

809
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:49,360
Once it's balanced, the pulp on top

810
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:50,920
will spread evenly.

811
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:54,600
Unevenness is what causes bubbles and such problems.

812
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:25,520
This time it's much better

813
00:41:33,080 --> 00:41:33,960
Lao Xuan

814
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:36,960
All that wrist practice paid off

815
00:41:38,320 --> 00:41:39,160
Much better now

816
00:41:48,960 --> 00:41:50,520
Compared to the last couple of days

817
00:41:51,800 --> 00:41:53,040
it really is much better

818
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:54,960
But Old Man

819
00:41:57,360 --> 00:41:59,440
it still doesn't meet the standard

820
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:03,640
You've got to keep practicing harder

821
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:04,520
Yes

822
00:42:14,160 --> 00:42:15,480
Fellow masters

823
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:19,040
For the Three-Zhang-Three

824
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:22,800
this Xuan paper none of us has ever seen

825
00:42:23,920 --> 00:42:25,480
we papermakers

826
00:42:26,360 --> 00:42:28,640
have been at it for over ten days now

827
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:34,240
We've come a long way from the start

828
00:42:34,520 --> 00:42:38,000
but the results still fall just short

829
00:42:39,640 --> 00:42:41,800
Not satisfying, not ideal

830
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:45,960
So do we just give up and surrender?

831
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:47,760
Do we just quit?

832
00:42:49,360 --> 00:42:52,040
Just like all of you masters

833
00:42:52,760 --> 00:42:54,960
I'm terribly anxious inside
